Go's runtime environment variables
1 Dec 2015
Tags: Runtime, Environment, @davecheney

Guillaume Laforge

* Summary

Dave Cheney offers a tour of the most useful and interesting environment variables which affect your Go programs:

- GOGC: for tweaking the garbage collection frequency
- GOTRACEBACK: to control the level of details of panic errors
- GOMAXPROCS: to specify the number of operating system threads allocated to goroutines in your program
- GODEBUG: for specifying certain handy debug traces

